/**
Syntax:
set the iconPresetName of <widget> to <pIconName>
get the iconPresetName of <widget>

Summary: A predefined SVG icon path names.

Parameters:
pIconName: The name of the icon to display.

Example: set the iconPresetName of widget "SVG Icon" to "thumbs up"

Description:
Use the <iconPresetName> property to set the icon of the widget to one of the
predefined graphics provided by the "IconSVG" or "libSVGicons" libraries.

You can get a list of available predefined path names by running
`put iconNames()` in the Message Box.
*/
property "iconPresetName" get mIconPresetName set setPathPreset
metadata iconPresetName.editor is "com.livecode.pi.svgicon"
metadata iconPresetName.default is "Puzzle Piece"
metadata iconPresetName.label is "Preset"

/**
Syntax:
get the iconName of <widget>

Example: put the iconName of widget "SVG Icon"

Summary: The name of the currently chosen icon.

Description:
use the <IconName> to get the name of the currently chosen icon.

You can get a list of available predefined path names by running
`put iconNames()` in the Message Box.
*/
property "iconName" get mIconPresetName
metadata iconName.label is "Icon Name"


/**
Syntax:
set the iconPath of <widget> to <pSVGPath>
get the iconPath of <widget>

Summary: The path data displayed by the SVG path widget.

Parameters:
pSVGPath: A string containing valid SVG path syntax.

Example:
-- Create a filled triangle
set the iconPath of widget "SVG Icon" to "M150 0 L75 200 L225 200 Z"

Description:
The SVG path string to be displayed by the SVG path widget.

See https://www.w3.org/TR/SVG/paths.html#PathData for the SVG path data
specification.
*/
property "iconPath" get mPath set setPath
metadata iconPath.editor is "com.livecode.pi.text"
metadata iconPath.label is "Path data"

/**
Syntax:
set the highlight of <widget> to {true|false}
get the highlight of <widget>

Summary: `true` if the SVG path is highlighted; `false` otherwise

Description:
Use the `highlight` property to test or control whether the SVG path is
displayed as highlighted or not.
*/
property "highlight" get mHilited set setIsHilited
metadata highlight.default is "false"
metadata highlight.label is "Hilited"
public handler setIsHilited(in pBoolean as Boolean)
	put pBoolean into mHilited
	redraw all
end handler

/**

Name: opaque

Syntax: set the opaque of <widget> to {true | false}
Syntax: get the opaque of <widget>

Summary: Whether the background is filled

Description:
If the <opaque> property is `true`, the background is filled with the <backColor>.

References: backColor (property)
**/
private variable mOpaque as Boolean
property "opaque" get mOpaque set setOpaque
metadata opaque.default is "true"
metadata opaque.label is "Opaque background"
private handler setOpaque(in pOpaque as Boolean) returns nothing
	if pOpaque is mOpaque then
		return
	end if
	put pOpaque into mOpaque
	redraw all
end handler

/**
Syntax:
set the maintainAspectRatio of <widget> to {true|false}
get the maintainAspectRatio of <widget>

Summary: Whether the SVG path maintains its aspect ratio when resized.

Description:
If the <maintainAspectRatio> of the SVG path is `true`, the icon will be its
maximum size within its bounds while maintaining the original ratio of width
to height. If `false`, it will stretch to fit the extent of its bounds.
*/
property "maintainAspectRatio"  get mMaintainAspectRatio  set setMaintainAspectRatio
metadata maintainAspectRatio.default is "true"
metadata maintainAspectRatio.label is "Fix aspect ratio"
public handler setMaintainAspectRatio(in pBoolean as Boolean)
	put pBoolean into mMaintainAspectRatio
	CalculateScaledSizes()
	redraw all
end handler

/**
Syntax:
get the scaledWidth of <widget>

Summary: The width of the bounding rect of the SVG path, in fractional pixels.

Description:
If the <maintainAspectRatio> of the SVG path is `true`, then the <scaledWidth>
of the object will return the width of the bounding rect of the SVG path.
Otherwise, it will return the width of the widget.

Related: scaledHeight(property), maintainAspectRatio(property)
*/
property "scaledWidth" get mScaledWidth

/**
Syntax:
get the scaledHeight of <widget>

Summary: The height of the bounding rect of the SVG path, in fractional pixels.

Description:
If the <maintainAspectRatio> of the SVG path is `true`, then the <scaledHeight>
of the object will return the height of the bounding rect of the SVG path.
Otherwise, it will return the height of the widget.

Related: scaledWidth(property), maintainAspectRatio(property)
*/
property "scaledHeight" get mScaledHeight

/**
Syntax:
set the angle of <widget> to <pAngle>
get the angle of <widget>

Summary: The angle of rotation of the SVG path, in degrees clockwise.

Description:
The <angle> property controls the angle of rotation of for the SVG path
around the centre of the path's bounding box.  The rotation is in clockwise
degrees.
*/
property "angle" get mAngle set setAngle
metadata angle.editor is "com.livecode.pi.number"
metadata angle.default is "0"
metadata angle.label is "Rotation"

/**
Syntax:
set the fillRule of <widget> to <pRule>
get the fillRule of <widget>

Parameters:
pRule(enum): The fill rule to be used.
- "non-zero": Fill regions encircled at least once by the path.
- "even odd": Fill regions encircled an even number of times by the path.

Summary: The fill rule to be used when rendering the SVG path.

Description:
Use the <fillRule> property to set the fill rule to be used for the widget.
You may need to adjust it to ensure that paths that cross themselves, and paths
that are made up of overlapping subpaths, are filled correctly.

The areas enclosed by the path are each filled or not filled depending on the
fill rule used and the number of times the path loops around them.  When the
path goes around a region clockwise, it adds 1 to number of encirclements.
When it goes around a region anticlockwise, it subtracs 1 from the number of
encirclements.

See https://www.w3.org/TR/SVG/painting.html#FillRuleProperty for examples of
the "non-zero" and "even odd" fill rules.
*/
private variable mFillRule as String
property "fillRule"       get mFillRule      set setFillRule
metadata fillRule.editor is "com.livecode.pi.enum"
metadata fillRule.options is "non-zero,even odd"
metadata fillRule.default is "non-zero"
metadata fillRule.label is "Fill rule"
public handler setFillRule(in pRule as String) returns nothing
	put pRule into mFillRule
	redraw all
end handler

-- called when widget is created
public handler OnCreate()
    put true into mOpaque
   --  put "" into mLabelText
	put 0 into mAngle
	put 1 into mBorderWidth
   put false into mHilited
   put true into mMaintainAspectRatio
   put false into mFlipVertically
   -- put nothing into mForegroundColor
   -- put nothing into mBackgroundColor
   -- put the color of my highlight paint into mHiliteColor
	put the color of my border paint into mBorderColor
   put the color of my border paint into mLabelTextColor
   -- put the color of my top paint into mLabelTextColor
	-- put the color of my background paint into mBackgroundColor
   -- variable tPaint
   -- put my foreground paint into tPaint
   -- log [tPaint]
   -- put the color of my foreground paint into mForegroundColor
   -- log [mForegroundColor]
   --else
   --   log [mForegroundPattern]
   --end if
   setFillGradient("0,0,0,0\n1,0,0,0")
	put "non-zero" into mFillRule
	setPathPreset("Puzzle Piece")
   -- get property "name" of my script object
   --  log the result
   redraw all
end handler
-- public handler OnOpen()
--   get property "name" of my script object
--   log the result
-- end handler

public handler OnSave(out rProperties as Array)
	put the empty array into rProperties
	put mIconPresetName into rProperties["iconPresetName"]
   put mPoints into rProperties["points"]
	put mPath into rProperties["iconPath"]
	put mBorderWidth into rProperties["borderWidth"]
	put mHilited into rProperties["hilited"]
	put mMaintainAspectRatio into rProperties["maintainAspectRatio"]
	put mFlipVertically into rProperties["flipped"]
	put mAngle into rProperties["angle"]
	put mFillRule into rProperties["fillRule"]
   put mBorderWidth into rProperties["borderWidth"]
   put mOpaque into rProperties["opaque"]
   put mLabelText into rProperties["label"]
   put mToolTip into rProperties["tooltip"]
   if mForegroundColor is not nothing then
	     put colorToString(mForegroundColor,false) into rProperties["foregroundColor"]
  end if
  if mForegroundPattern is not nothing then
     put mForegroundPattern into rProperties["foregroundPattern"]
  end if
   if mBackgroundColor is not nothing then
      put colorToString(mBackgroundColor,false) into rProperties["backgroundColor"]
   end if
   put mBackgroundPattern into rProperties["backgroundPattern"]
   if mBorderColor is not nothing then
      put colorToString(mBorderColor,false) into rProperties["borderColor"]
   end if
   put mBorderPattern into rProperties["borderPattern"]
   if mHiliteColor is not nothing then
      put colorToString(mHiliteColor,false) into rProperties["hiliteColor"]
   end if
   if mHilitePattern is not nothing then
      put mHilitePattern into rProperties["hilitePattern"]
   end if
   if mLabelTextColor is not nothing then
       put colorToString(mLabelTextColor,false) into rProperties["labelTextColor"]
   end if
   if mFillGradient is not nothing then
      put mFillGradient into rProperties["fillGradient"]
   end if
end handler

public handler OnLoad(in pProperties as Array)
   put pProperties["iconPresetName"] into mIconPresetName
   put pProperties["points"] into mPoints
   setPoints(mPoints)
   put pProperties["iconPath"] into mPath

	put pProperties["borderWidth"] into mBorderWidth
   put pProperties["hilited"] into mHilited

   if "fillRule" is among the keys of pProperties then
      put pProperties["fillRule"] into mFillRule
   end if
   if "maintain aspect ratio" is among the keys of pProperties then
      put pProperties["maintainAspectRatio"] into mMaintainAspectRatio
   end if
   if "flipped" is among the keys of pProperties then
      put pProperties["flipped"] into mFlipVertically
   end if
   if "angle" is among the keys of pProperties then
      put pProperties["angle"] into mAngle
   end if
   if "opaque" is among the keys of pProperties then
      put pProperties["opaque"] into mOpaque
   end if
   if "label" is among the keys of pProperties then
      put pProperties["label"] into mLabelText
   end if
   if "tooltip" is among the keys of pProperties then
      put pProperties["tooltip"] into mToolTip
   end if
	-- Older SVG widgets do not have this property
	if "fillRule" is among the keys of pProperties then
		put pProperties["fillRule"] into mFillRule
	end if
   if "foregroundColor" is among the keys of pProperties then
	     put stringToColor(pProperties["foregroundColor"]) into mForegroundColor
  end if
  if "foregroundPattern" is among the keys of pProperties then
     put pProperties["foregroundPattern"] into mForegroundPattern
   end if
   if "backgroundColor" is among the keys of pProperties then
      put stringToColor(pProperties["backgroundColor"]) into mBackgroundColor
    end if
    if "backgroundPattern" is among the keys of pProperties then
      put pProperties["backgroundPattern"] into mBackgroundPattern
    end if
   if "borderColor" is among the keys of pProperties then
      put stringToColor(pProperties["borderColor"]) into mBorderColor
    end if
   if "borderPattern" is among the keys of pProperties then
     put pProperties["borderPattern"] into mBorderPattern
   end if
   if "hiliteColor" is among the keys of pProperties then
      put stringToColor(pProperties["hiliteColor"]) into mHiliteColor
    end if
   if "hilitePattern" is among the keys of pProperties then
      put pProperties["hilitePattern"] into mHilitePattern
   end if
   if "labelTextColor" is among the keys of pProperties then
      put stringToColor(pProperties["labelTextColor"]) into mLabelTextColor
   end if
   if "fillGradient" is among the keys of pProperties then
      put pProperties["fillGradient"] into mFillGradient
      setFillGradient(mFillGradient)
   end if
	CalculateScaledSizes()
   redraw all
end handler
----------
/*
put mTextFont into rProperties["textFont"]
put mTextSize into rProperties["textSize"]
put mLabel into rProperties["label"]
put mIconImageFilePath into rProperties["iconImageFilePath"]
put mIconImageText into rProperties["iconImageText"]
*/

-- this handler is called when the widget is resized
public handler OnGeometryChanged()
    if my width is not mWidth or my height is not mHeight then
        CalculateScaledSizes()
        put my width into mWidth
        put my height into mHeight
    end if
    redraw all
end handler

-- the following handlers deal with mouse events
public handler OnMouseUp()
	if the click count is 2 then
		post "mouseDoubleUp" with [the click button formatted as string]
	else
		post "mouseUp" with [the click button formatted as string]
	end if
end handler

public handler OnMouseDown()
	post "mouseDown" with [the click button formatted as string]
end handler

public handler OnMouseEnter()
	post "mouseEnter"
end handler

public handler OnMouseLeave()
	post "mouseLeave"
end handler

/**
Syntax:
set the flipped of <widget> to {true|false}
get the flipped of <widget>

Summary: `true` if the SVG path is flipped top-to-bottom; `false` otherwise

Description:
When <flipped> is set to `true`, the SVG path is drawn upside down.
*/
property "flipped" get mFlipVertically set setFlipVertically
metadata flipped.default is "false"
metadata flipped.label is "Flip"
public handler setFlipVertically(in pBoolean as Boolean)
	put pBoolean into mFlipVertically
	redraw all
end handler

public handler setPath(in pPath as String) returns nothing
	put pPath into mPath
	put "" into mIconPresetName
	CalculateScaledSizes()
	redraw all
end handler


variable mPoints as String
property "points" get mPoints set setPoints
metadata points.editor is "com.livecode.pi.text"
metadata points.default is ""
metadata points.label is "Points"
public handler setPoints(in pPoints as String) returns nothing
	variable tOriginalPointsList as List
	variable tContinuousLine as  String
	variable tContinuousLineList as List
	variable tContinuousLinePoints as List
	variable tLinePoint as String
	variable tLineSVGPath as String
	variable tLineSVGLines as String
	put pPoints into mPoints
   if pPoints is not "" then
      setPathPreset("")

      split mPoints by "\n\n" into tOriginalPointsList
      repeat for each element tContinuousLine in tOriginalPointsList
         split tContinuousLine by "\n" into tContinuousLinePoints
         -- log  tContinuousLinePoints
         put "M"  into tLineSVGPath
      	repeat for each element tLinePoint in tContinuousLinePoints
             -- should go a strep further here and check that items of point are actually integers
      	       put tLinePoint & " L" after tLineSVGPath
      	end repeat
      	delete char -2 to -1 of tLineSVGPath
      	put "Z " after tLineSVGPath
         put tLineSVGPath & "\n" after tLineSVGLines
      end repeat
      replace "\n" with " " in tLineSVGLines
      delete char -1 of tLineSVGLines
      -- log tLineSVGLines
      put tLineSVGLines into mPath
      put "" into mIconPresetName
   end if
	CalculateScaledSizes()
	redraw all
end handler

public handler setPathPreset(in pPresetName as String) returns nothing
	put iconSVGPathFromName(pPresetName) into mPath
	put pPresetName into mIconPresetName
	CalculateScaledSizes()
	redraw all
end handler

public handler setAngle(in pAngle as Number) returns nothing
	put pAngle into mAngle
	CalculateScaledSizes()
	redraw all
end handler

-- called whenever LiveCode needs to redraw the widget
public handler OnPaint()
   variable tPath as Path
   variable tGradient
   /*
   if mGradientRamp is not nothing then
   -- if mGradientRamp is not empty then
         variable tGradient as Gradient
         put linear gradient with ramp mGradientRamp into tGradient
         -- put rectangle path of my bounds into tPath
         set the from of tGradient to point [the right of my bounds / 2,0]
         set the to of tGradient to point [the right of my bounds / 2, the bottom of my bounds /2]
         -- set the via of tGradient to point [the left of my bounds / 2, the bottom of my bounds]
         add rectangle path of my bounds to this canvas
         set the paint of this canvas to tGradient
         fill this canvas
   end if
  */
	put path mPath into tPath

	variable tBounds
	if mFlipVertically then
		scale tPath by [1,-1]
		translate tPath by [0, the height of the bounding box of tPath]
	end if

	if mAngle > 0 then
		rotate tPath by mAngle
	end if

	// scale to fit within widget and maintain aspect ratio
	if mMaintainAspectRatio then
		variable tNewPathRect as Rectangle
		put rectangle [ 0 + (mBorderWidth/2), 0 + (mBorderWidth/2), the width of my bounds - (mBorderWidth/2) , the height of my bounds - (mBorderWidth/2) ] into tNewPathRect
		constrainPathToRect( tNewPathRect, tPath)
		-- 	constrainPathToRect(my bounds, tPath)
	else
		scale tPath by [ (my width - mBorderWidth) / (the width of the bounding box of tPath ), \
				(my height - mBorderWidth) / (the height of the bounding box of tPath ) ]
		put the bounding box of tPath into tBounds
		translate tPath by [(the left of tBounds * -1) + (mBorderWidth/2), (the top of tBounds * -1) + (mBorderWidth/2)]
	end if

	if mOpaque then
		if mHilited is false then
			set the paint of this canvas to my foreground paint
		else
			set the paint of this canvas to my highlight paint
		end if
		set the fill rule of this canvas to mFillRule
		fill tPath on this canvas
	end if
	set the stroke width of this canvas to mBorderWidth
	set the paint of this canvas to my border paint
	stroke tPath on this canvas
   if mLabelText is not nothing then
      set the font of this canvas to my font
      if mLabelTextColor is not empty then
         set the paint of this canvas to solid paint with mLabelTextColor
         -- if mTextAlign is "center" then
         fill text mLabelText at center of my bounds on this canvas
      else
         set the paint of this canvas to my top paint -- my border paint? my topColor paint? What are the others?
         fill text mLabelText at center of my bounds on this canvas
      end if
      -- if mGradientRamp is not nothing then
      if mGradientRamp is not empty then
            put linear gradient with ramp mGradientRamp into tGradient
            -- put rectangle path of my bounds into tPath
            set the from of tGradient to point [the right of my bounds / 2,0]
            set the to of tGradient to point [the right of my bounds / 2, the bottom of my bounds /2]
            -- set the via of tGradient to point [the left of my bounds / 2, the bottom of my bounds]
            set the paint of this canvas to tGradient
            fill text mLabelText at center of my bounds on this canvas
      end if
      -- stroke text mLabelText at center of my bounds on this canvas --- wish this syntax worked, it does not
		--   fill text mLabel at point [ the width of tLabelRect /2 , my height / 2 + 4 ] on this canvas
		-- 	fill text mLabel at point [ my width / 2 , my height / 2 ] on this canvas
		--     end if
		-- put 0 into  mLabelLocHorizontalOffset
		-- put 0 into  mLabelLocHVerticalOffset
	end if
end handler

-- used in various places to calculate the scaledWidth & scaledHeight variables
private handler CalculateScaledSizes()
	//recalculate the bounding box for the path
	variable tPath as Path
	variable tNewPathRect as Rectangle
	put path mPath into tPath
	if mMaintainAspectRatio then
		put rectangle [ 0 + mBorderWidth, 0 + mBorderWidth, the width of my bounds - mBorderWidth , the width of my bounds - mBorderWidth ] into tNewPathRect
		constrainPathToRect( tNewPathRect, tPath)
		put the width of the bounding box of tPath - (mBorderWidth *2) into mScaledWidth
		put the height of the bounding box of tPath - (mBorderWidth *2) into mScaledHeight
	else
		put my width - (mBorderWidth *2) into mScaledWidth
		put my height - (mBorderWidth *2) into mScaledHeight
	end if
end handler

end widget
